title: American_Top_40_1983_February_26th
description:
American Top 40 with Casey Kasem aired on radio from July 4, 1970 until August 6, 1988. This is a recording of a rebroadcast from internet radio.

In this broadcast:

Bands appearing with their first chart hits inlude Night Ranger, Duran Duran, Culture Club, and the Stray Cats.
	
Casey answers the question, "Who was the first black recording act in chart history to hit the top ten?"

Casey recounts the origin of the Wedding March.

A listener wants to know, "What recording act has had the shortest name?" There have been two whose name consisted of only one letter.
